translated: Kjellin, Ester Maria (Maja), licensed physician, Gothenburg, born on 4/2/98 in Örebro to factory worker Hjalmar Jansson and Julia Lundbäck. Married on 24 [unknown month] to city physician in Lidköping, med. iic. Gösta Kjellin. Children: Anders, born in 1924, became a lieutenant in the engineering corps, married in 1946 to Margit Ahlbom from Mölndal; Bror, born in 1927, studying; Kerstin, born in 1929, also studying; Birgit, born in 1931, studying. Completed secondary school exams in Stockholm in 1917, medical bachelor's degree at the Karolinska Institute in 1920, medical licentiate in Lund in 1928, philosophy bachelor's degree in Gothenburg in 1946. Assistant physician and acting deputy physician and chief physician at Sachsska Children's Hospital in 1926, acting assistant chief medical officer and medical officer in the Mariestad district, and acting city physician in Mariestad in 1927, acting medical officer in the Björkvik and Mariestad districts in 1928. Worked as a physician for the medical experimentation for prenatal and postnatal care for childbirth in Lidköping from 1931 to 1934, practical physician there from 1929 to 1939.
